import React from 'react'

function NavBar() {

    return ( <
        div >
        <
        nav class = "navbar navbar-expand-lg navbar-light bg-light shadow" >

        <
        div class = "container" >

        <
        a href = "/"
        class = "navbar-brand" >
        <
        img src = "assets/logo.png"
        width = "100px" / >
        <
        /a> <
        button class = "navbar-toggler"
        type = "button"
        dataToggle = "collapse"
        dataTarget = "#navbarResponsive"
        ariaControls = "navbarResponsive"
        ariaExpanded = "false"
        ariaEabel = "Toggle navigation" >
        <
        span class = "navbar-toggler-icon" > < /span> <
        /button> <
        div class = "collapse navbar-collapse"
        id = "navbarResponsive" >
        <
        ul class = "navbar-nav ml-auto" >
        <
        li class = "nav-item active" >
        <
        a href = "/"
        class = "nav-link" >
        <
        i class = "fas fa-home" > < /i> <
        span class = "p-2" > Home < /span> <
        span class = "sr-only" > (current) < /span> <
        /a> <
        /li> <
        li class = "nav-item" >
        <
        a href = "/developers"
        class = "nav-link" >
        <
        span class = "p-2" > Our Developers < /span> <
        /a> <
        /li> <
        li class = "nav-item" >
        <
        a href = "/projects"
        class = "nav-link" >
        <
        span class = "p-2" > Projects < /span> <
        /a> <
        /li>

        <
        li class = "nav-item" >
        <
        a href = "/blog"
        class = "nav-link" >
        <
        i class = "far fa-comment" > < /i> <
        span class = "p-2" > Blog < /span> <
        /a> <
        /li>

        <
        /ul> <
        /div> <
        /div>

        <
        /nav>

        <
        /div>
    )
}

export default NavBar
